-- Generali Plans to Form International Board, Italy Manager, La Stampa Says
-- B y   D a n   L i e f g r e e n
-- 2010-10-30T09:28:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-30/generali-plans-to-form-international-board-italy-manager-la-stampa-says.html
Assicurazioni Generali SpA  plans to
create an international management board and a new position of
country manager for Italy, daily  La Stampa  reported, without
saying where it got the information.  Chief Executive Officer  Giovanni Perissinotto  will discuss
the matters at a Nov. 4 meeting of the insurer’s executive
committee in Rome, the newspaper said. The company’s board of
directors will review Perissinotto’s proposals Nov. 11, La
Stampa said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Dan Liefgreen  in Milan at 
 dliefgreen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tim Quinson at 
 tquinson@bloomberg.net  